By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Former President Goodluck Jonathan has greeted the Muslim Ummah on the occasion of their Eid-el-Kabir celebration, urging the to prioritize the virtues of sacrifice, tolerance and love that this moment signifies. Jonathan who made the call in a statemnt released via his Facebook page, charged all citizens to pray for the peace of our nation, adding that this moment demands of all, irrespective of tribe and faith, to show love and promote those virtues that will foster our unity and enhance progress. The statement reads in full: Congratulations to the Muslim Ummah on this year’s Eid-El-Kabir. I call on all Muslim faithful to prioritize the virtues of sacrifice, tolerance and love which this moment signifies. I urge all citizens to pray for the peace of our nation; this moment demands of all, irrespective of tribe and faith, to show love and promote those virtues that will foster our unity and enhance progress.Barka Da Sallah By ADEYEMI ADELEYE LAGOS- The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Lagos State says it shares in the plight of Muslim faithful over the high cost of food and items on the occasion of the 2022 Eid-el-Kabir.Wishing the Muslims Eid AL-Adha Mubarak, the party in a statement by its Publicity Secretary,… In "News" By OLUWATOPE LAWANSON Senator Bola Tinubu LAGOS- APC 2023 Presidential Candidate, Sen. Bola Tinubu has urged Muslim faithful to always strive to conduct their daily lives in accordance with the clear and beneficial message of Eid.Tinubu in a statement by his media spokesperson Mr Tunde Rahman, on Friday in Lagos, … In "News" By YAHAYA ISAH ABUJA- The Federal Government has declared Monday and Tuesday as public holidays to mark this year’s Eid-el-Kabir celebration.This is contained in a statement issued by the Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Interior, Dr Shuaib Belgore, on Thursday in Abuja.Belgore said the Minister of Interior,   Rauf Aregbesola,  who made… In "News"